data.title: ANNA: the cult 1967 film starring Anna Karina and Serge Gainsbourg is back in theaters!
data.meta_description: Discover ANNA: the cult film by Anna Karina and Serge Gainsbourg finally in theaters on November 29, 2023. Don't miss this romantic musical comedy, never before seen in theaters, notably in Paris at Champo - Espace Jacques Tati, in the 5th arrondissement.
data.text:
The romantic musical ANNA arrives in cinemas for the very first time on November 29, 2023. This long-awaited event promises a unique incursion into the world of French New Wave pop art.

ANNA, starring Anna Karina, Serge Gainsbourg and Jean-Claude Brialy, is a romantic musical comedy. This authentic musical, created for the first time for the big screen, bears the signature of Serge Gainsbourg's musical and literary genius, dedicated to the talented Anna Karina. Accompanied by Pierre Koralnik, Philippe Katerine, Laurent Balandras and many distinguished guests, this first cinema outing promises to be simply unforgettable.

The story ofANNA plunges us into an idyllic encounter between Anna, who arrives in Paris, and Serge, who falls head over heels in love as soon as he steps off the train. Serge, the director of an advertising agency, in a bid to find the mysterious woman who has unleashed his ardent love, plasters the only photo of her all over the streets of Paris. An initiatory game of hide-and-seek ensues, giving life to exquisite, moving scenes.

Witness to a golden era in French cinema, ANNA is a veritable fusion of New Wave and pop art. Influenced by Godard and Truffaut, the film features Koralnik's inventive direction, Gainsbourg's unforgettable composition and the artistry of Karina and Brialy. A cinematic experience not to be missed!

Add to this Victor Upshaw's colorful choreography, tinged with anti-militarism, and the film is transformed into a lively, committed musical. The whole is sublimated by creative direction, exploiting city lights, neon lights and mirrors. As for Gainsbourg, he signs a very pop soundtrack, infusing all his modernity with the originality of his lyrics and musical composition. ANNA is undeniably a film of ceaseless movement, color and music.
